cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and deep learning techniques for detecting reflection and rotation symmetries in images. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses novel methods to convert human labels into symmetry heatmaps, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates Sym-NET against multiple existing computer vision algorithms, which involves graph theory and optimization techniques, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) another possible sub-category.
